  "body": "<!--💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎\r\n\r\nHellooo! 😄 \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\n💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎-->\r\n\r\n# 🚀 Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n<!-- ✍️ A clear and concise description of the problem or missing capability... -->\r\n\r\nHello,\r\n\r\nI think it would be nice to be able to use some custom directory for the slasher.\r\n\r\nFor example, in my case I want to use the Slasher in another nvme because of the high disk usage it generates and I prefer not to have it on the same disk as the beaconchain db.\r\n\r\nWith docker I have mounted the datadir to a directory but I can't mount a volume with only the slasher.db because all the directory is already assigned.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncommand:\r\n      - --accept-terms-of-use\r\n      - --datadir=/data\r\nvolumes:\r\n      - ./beacon/:/data\r\n      - ./slasher/slasher.db:/data/beaconchain/slasher.db   (not mounted because the entire directory is already mounted)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\n<!-- ✍️ If you have a solution in mind, please describe it. --> \r\n\r\ncreate a new parameter to specify the directory.\r\n\r\nfor example:\r\n> --slasher-datadir\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks !",
